# 📘 HTML Basic Questions Repository

This contains **basic HTML questions/projects** designed for beginners to learn and practice core web development concepts.

---

## 🎯 Objective

The goal of this is to provide hands-on practice of HTML fundamentals through small and simple question-based files. Each file focuses on a specific concept of HTML.

---

## 📚 List of HTML Questions / Files

1. Hello World HTML Page  
2. My First Webpage (Basic Structure)  
3. Ordered and Unordered Lists  
4. Simple HTML Table  
5. Hyperlinks (Anchor Tag Practice)  
6. Image Display in HTML  
7. Background Color Styling  
8. Font Styling (Color & Size)  
9. Login Form (Basic Input Fields)  
10. Radio Buttons & Checkboxes  
11. Dropdown Menu (Select Tag)  
12. Audio Player in HTML  
13. Video Player in HTML  
14. Marquee Scrolling Text  
15. Colored Table with Styling  

---

## 🧠 What You Will Learn

By practicing these questions, you will understand:

- Basic HTML structure
- Common HTML tags and attributes
- Form creation and input handling
- Media embedding (audio/video)
- Table and list creation
- Simple styling using HTML

